There were two large downy beds on quaintly wrought bedsteads of brass, but the two captives decided to sleep together.
Thorndyke was the first to awaken.
The lights in the candelabrum were out, but a gray light came in at the top and bottom of the window.
He rose and drew the heavy curtain of one of the windows aside.
